There are three <a href=\"\/node\/342\">types of mesothelioma<\/a>, all of which target the mesothelium, a layer of tissue that covers a majority of your internal organs.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most common form of mesothelioma is <a href=\"\/node\/343\">pleural mesothelioma<\/a>, which attacks the mesothelium known as the pleura that surrounds each lung. However, mesothelioma may also occur in peritoneum (the lining of the abdominal cavity) or the pericardium (the membrane around the heart).<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unlike some cancers, mesothelioma is difficult to detect in its infancy. <a href=\"\/node\/346\">Mesothelioma symptoms<\/a> are typically not apparent for at least 20 years and often upward of 40 years after exposure to asbestos.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many initial signs of mesothelioma&mdash;such as shortness of breath and chest pain&mdash;are shared with numerous other medical conditions, which complicates accurate early diagnosis. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/node\/348\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and&mdash;importantly&mdash;low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/node\/353\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. Because asbestos fibers are easily transferred, family members of those who worked with asbestos and brought asbestos dust home on their clothes have been known to develop mesothelioma from <a href=\"\/node\/360\">second-hand asbestos exposure<\/a>.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you or a family member was diagnosed with mesothelioma, please <a href=\"\/node\/326\">contact The Williams Law Firm, P.C.<\/a>&nbsp;online or call 855-955-MESO (6376) for your free consultation. There are three <a href=\"\/types-mesothelioma.html\">types of mesothelioma<\/a>, all of which target the mesothelium, a layer of tissue that covers a majority of your internal organs.<\/p>\n<p>The most common form of mesothelioma is <a href=\"\/pleural-mesothelioma.html\">pleural mesothelioma<\/a>, which attacks the mesothelium known as the pleura that surrounds each lung. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-treatment.html\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and\u2014importantly\u2014low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/asbestos-lung-cancer.html\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. Because asbestos fibers are easily transferred, family members of those who worked with asbestos and brought asbestos dust home on their clothes have been known to develop mesothelioma from <a href=\"\/second-hand-asbestos.html\">second-hand asbestos exposure<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>If you or a family member was diagnosed with mesothelioma, please <a href=\"\/contact-us.html\">contact The Williams Law Firm, P.C.<\/a>\u00a0online or call 855-955-MESO (6376) for your free consultation. There are three <a href=\"\/node\/342\">types of mesothelioma<\/a>, all of which target the mesothelium, a layer of tissue that covers a majority of your internal organs.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most common form of mesothelioma is <a href=\"\/node\/343\">pleural mesothelioma<\/a>, which attacks the mesothelium known as the pleura that surrounds each lung. However, mesothelioma may also occur in peritoneum (the lining of the abdominal cavity) or the pericardium (the membrane around the heart).<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unlike some cancers, mesothelioma is difficult to detect in its infancy. <a href=\"\/node\/346\">Mesothelioma symptoms<\/a> are typically not apparent for at least 20 years and often upward of 40 years after exposure to asbestos.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many initial signs of mesothelioma&mdash;such as shortness of breath and chest pain&mdash;are shared with numerous other medical conditions, which complicates accurate early diagnosis. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/node\/348\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and&mdash;importantly&mdash;low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/node\/353\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. Because asbestos fibers are easily transferred, family members of those who worked with asbestos and brought asbestos dust home on their clothes have been known to develop mesothelioma from <a href=\"\/node\/360\">second-hand asbestos exposure<\/a>.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you or a family member was diagnosed with mesothelioma, please <a href=\"\/node\/326\">contact The Williams Law Firm, P.C.<\/a>&nbsp;online or call 855-955-MESO (6376) for your free consultation. There are three <a href=\"\/types-mesothelioma.html\">types of mesothelioma<\/a>, all of which target the mesothelium, a layer of tissue that covers a majority of your internal organs.<\/p>\n<p>The most common form of mesothelioma is <a href=\"\/pleural-mesothelioma.html\">pleural mesothelioma<\/a>, which attacks the mesothelium known as the pleura that surrounds each lung. However, mesothelioma may also occur in peritoneum (the lining of the abdominal cavity) or the pericardium (the membrane around the heart).<\/p>\n<p>Unlike some cancers, mesothelioma is difficult to detect in its infancy. <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-symptoms.html\">Mesothelioma symptoms<\/a> are typically not apparent for at least 20 years and often upward of 40 years after exposure to asbestos.<\/p>\n<p>Many initial signs of mesothelioma\u2014such as shortness of breath and chest pain\u2014are shared with numerous other medical conditions, which complicates accurate early diagnosis. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-treatment.html\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and\u2014importantly\u2014low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/asbestos-lung-cancer.html\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. There are three <a href=\"\/types-mesothelioma.html\">types of mesothelioma<\/a>, all of which target the mesothelium, a layer of tissue that covers a majority of your internal organs.<\/p>\n<p>The most common form of mesothelioma is <a href=\"\/pleural-mesothelioma.html\">pleural mesothelioma<\/a>, which attacks the mesothelium known as the pleura that surrounds each lung. However, mesothelioma may also occur in peritoneum (the lining of the abdominal cavity) or the pericardium (the membrane around the heart).<\/p>\n<p>Unlike some cancers, mesothelioma is difficult to detect in its infancy. <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-symptoms.html\">Mesothelioma symptoms<\/a> are typically not apparent for at least 20 years and often upward of 40 years after exposure to asbestos.<\/p>\n<p>Many initial signs of mesothelioma\u2014such as shortness of breath and chest pain\u2014are shared with numerous other medical conditions, which complicates accurate early diagnosis. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-treatment.html\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and\u2014importantly\u2014low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/asbestos-lung-cancer.html\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. Because asbestos fibers are easily transferred, family members of those who worked with asbestos and brought asbestos dust home on their clothes have been known to develop mesothelioma from <a href=\"\/second-hand-asbestos.html\">second-hand asbestos exposure<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>If you or a family member was diagnosed with mesothelioma, please <a href=\"\/contact-us.html\">contact The Williams Law Firm, P.C.<\/a>\u00a0online or call 855-955-MESO (6376) for your free consultation. New York attorney Joseph P. Williams has a proven record of success helping mesothelioma victims and their families from Manhattan, the Bronx, Queens, Staten Island and across the United States recover the money they need and peace of mind they deserve.<\/p>\n","safe_summary":"<div class=\"node node-type-page clearfix\" id=\"node-24\">\n<div class=\"content\">\n<div There are three <a href=\"\/node\/342\">types of mesothelioma<\/a>, all of which target the mesothelium, a layer of tissue that covers a majority of your internal organs.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most common form of mesothelioma is <a href=\"\/node\/343\">pleural mesothelioma<\/a>, which attacks the mesothelium known as the pleura that surrounds each lung. However, mesothelioma may also occur in peritoneum (the lining of the abdominal cavity) or the pericardium (the membrane around the heart).<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unlike some cancers, mesothelioma is difficult to detect in its infancy. <a href=\"\/node\/346\">Mesothelioma symptoms<\/a> are typically not apparent for at least 20 years and often upward of 40 years after exposure to asbestos.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many initial signs of mesothelioma&mdash;such as shortness of breath and chest pain&mdash;are shared with numerous other medical conditions, which complicates accurate early diagnosis. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/node\/348\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and&mdash;importantly&mdash;low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/node\/353\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. Because asbestos fibers are easily transferred, family members of those who worked with asbestos and brought asbestos dust home on their clothes have been known to develop mesothelioma from <a href=\"\/node\/360\">second-hand asbestos exposure<\/a>.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you or a family member was diagnosed with mesothelioma, please <a href=\"\/node\/326\">contact The Williams Law Firm, P.C.<\/a>&nbsp;online or call 855-955-MESO (6376) for your free consultation. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-treatment.html\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and\u2014importantly\u2014low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/asbestos-lung-cancer.html\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. There are three <a href=\"\/node\/342\">types of mesothelioma<\/a>, all of which target the mesothelium, a layer of tissue that covers a majority of your internal organs.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most common form of mesothelioma is <a href=\"\/node\/343\">pleural mesothelioma<\/a>, which attacks the mesothelium known as the pleura that surrounds each lung. However, mesothelioma may also occur in peritoneum (the lining of the abdominal cavity) or the pericardium (the membrane around the heart).<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unlike some cancers, mesothelioma is difficult to detect in its infancy. <a href=\"\/node\/346\">Mesothelioma symptoms<\/a> are typically not apparent for at least 20 years and often upward of 40 years after exposure to asbestos.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many initial signs of mesothelioma&mdash;such as shortness of breath and chest pain&mdash;are shared with numerous other medical conditions, which complicates accurate early diagnosis. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/node\/348\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and&mdash;importantly&mdash;low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/node\/353\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. Because asbestos fibers are easily transferred, family members of those who worked with asbestos and brought asbestos dust home on their clothes have been known to develop mesothelioma from <a href=\"\/node\/360\">second-hand asbestos exposure<\/a>.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you or a family member was diagnosed with mesothelioma, please <a href=\"\/node\/326\">contact The Williams Law Firm, P.C.<\/a>&nbsp;online or call 855-955-MESO (6376) for your free consultation. There are three <a href=\"\/types-mesothelioma.html\">types of mesothelioma<\/a>, all of which target the mesothelium, a layer of tissue that covers a majority of your internal organs.<\/p>\n<p>The most common form of mesothelioma is <a href=\"\/pleural-mesothelioma.html\">pleural mesothelioma<\/a>, which attacks the mesothelium known as the pleura that surrounds each lung. However, mesothelioma may also occur in peritoneum (the lining of the abdominal cavity) or the pericardium (the membrane around the heart).<\/p>\n<p>Unlike some cancers, mesothelioma is difficult to detect in its infancy. <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-symptoms.html\">Mesothelioma symptoms<\/a> are typically not apparent for at least 20 years and often upward of 40 years after exposure to asbestos.<\/p>\n<p>Many initial signs of mesothelioma\u2014such as shortness of breath and chest pain\u2014are shared with numerous other medical conditions, which complicates accurate early diagnosis. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-treatment.html\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and\u2014importantly\u2014low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/asbestos-lung-cancer.html\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. Because asbestos fibers are easily transferred, family members of those who worked with asbestos and brought asbestos dust home on their clothes have been known to develop mesothelioma from <a href=\"\/second-hand-asbestos.html\">second-hand asbestos exposure<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>If you or a family member was diagnosed with mesothelioma, please <a href=\"\/contact-us.html\">contact The Williams Law Firm, P.C.<\/a>\u00a0online or call 855-955-MESO (6376) for your free consultation. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-treatment.html\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and\u2014importantly\u2014low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/asbestos-lung-cancer.html\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. Because asbestos fibers are easily transferred, family members of those who worked with asbestos and brought asbestos dust home on their clothes have been known to develop mesothelioma from <a href=\"\/second-hand-asbestos.html\">second-hand asbestos exposure<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>If you or a family member was diagnosed with mesothelioma, please <a href=\"\/contact-us.html\">contact The Williams Law Firm, P.C.<\/a>\u00a0online or call 855-955-MESO (6376) for your free consultation. There are three <a href=\"\/node\/342\">types of mesothelioma<\/a>, all of which target the mesothelium, a layer of tissue that covers a majority of your internal organs.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most common form of mesothelioma is <a href=\"\/node\/343\">pleural mesothelioma<\/a>, which attacks the mesothelium known as the pleura that surrounds each lung. However, mesothelioma may also occur in peritoneum (the lining of the abdominal cavity) or the pericardium (the membrane around the heart).<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unlike some cancers, mesothelioma is difficult to detect in its infancy. <a href=\"\/node\/346\">Mesothelioma symptoms<\/a> are typically not apparent for at least 20 years and often upward of 40 years after exposure to asbestos.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many initial signs of mesothelioma&mdash;such as shortness of breath and chest pain&mdash;are shared with numerous other medical conditions, which complicates accurate early diagnosis. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/node\/348\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and&mdash;importantly&mdash;low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/node\/353\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. Because asbestos fibers are easily transferred, family members of those who worked with asbestos and brought asbestos dust home on their clothes have been known to develop mesothelioma from <a href=\"\/node\/360\">second-hand asbestos exposure<\/a>.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you or a family member was diagnosed with mesothelioma, please <a href=\"\/node\/326\">contact The Williams Law Firm, P.C.<\/a>&nbsp;online or call 855-955-MESO (6376) for your free consultation. There are three <a href=\"\/types-mesothelioma.html\">types of mesothelioma<\/a>, all of which target the mesothelium, a layer of tissue that covers a majority of your internal organs.<\/p>\n<p>The most common form of mesothelioma is <a href=\"\/pleural-mesothelioma.html\">pleural mesothelioma<\/a>, which attacks the mesothelium known as the pleura that surrounds each lung. However, mesothelioma may also occur in peritoneum (the lining of the abdominal cavity) or the pericardium (the membrane around the heart).<\/p>\n<p>Unlike some cancers, mesothelioma is difficult to detect in its infancy. <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-symptoms.html\">Mesothelioma symptoms<\/a> are typically not apparent for at least 20 years and often upward of 40 years after exposure to asbestos.<\/p>\n<p>Many initial signs of mesothelioma\u2014such as shortness of breath and chest pain\u2014are shared with numerous other medical conditions, which complicates accurate early diagnosis. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-treatment.html\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and\u2014importantly\u2014low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/asbestos-lung-cancer.html\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-treatment.html\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and\u2014importantly\u2014low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/asbestos-lung-cancer.html\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. Because asbestos fibers are easily transferred, family members of those who worked with asbestos and brought asbestos dust home on their clothes have been known to develop mesothelioma from <a href=\"\/second-hand-asbestos.html\">second-hand asbestos exposure<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>If you or a family member was diagnosed with mesothelioma, please <a href=\"\/contact-us.html\">contact The Williams Law Firm, P.C.<\/a>\u00a0online or call 855-955-MESO (6376) for your free consultation. New York attorney Joseph P. Williams has a proven record of success helping mesothelioma victims and their families from Manhattan, the Bronx, Queens, Staten Island and across the United States recover the money they need and There are three <a href=\"\/node\/342\">types of mesothelioma<\/a>, all of which target the mesothelium, a layer of tissue that covers a majority of your internal organs.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>The most common form of mesothelioma is <a href=\"\/node\/343\">pleural mesothelioma<\/a>, which attacks the mesothelium known as the pleura that surrounds each lung. However, mesothelioma may also occur in peritoneum (the lining of the abdominal cavity) or the pericardium (the membrane around the heart).<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unlike some cancers, mesothelioma is difficult to detect in its infancy. <a href=\"\/node\/346\">Mesothelioma symptoms<\/a> are typically not apparent for at least 20 years and often upward of 40 years after exposure to asbestos.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many initial signs of mesothelioma&mdash;such as shortness of breath and chest pain&mdash;are shared with numerous other medical conditions, which complicates accurate early diagnosis. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/node\/348\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and&mdash;importantly&mdash;low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/node\/353\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. Because asbestos fibers are easily transferred, family members of those who worked with asbestos and brought asbestos dust home on their clothes have been known to develop mesothelioma from <a href=\"\/node\/360\">second-hand asbestos exposure<\/a>.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you or a family member was diagnosed with mesothelioma, please <a href=\"\/node\/326\">contact The Williams Law Firm, P.C.<\/a>&nbsp;online or call 855-955-MESO (6376) for your free consultation. There are three <a href=\"\/types-mesothelioma.html\">types of mesothelioma<\/a>, all of which target the mesothelium, a layer of tissue that covers a majority of your internal organs.<\/p>\n<p>The most common form of mesothelioma is <a href=\"\/pleural-mesothelioma.html\">pleural mesothelioma<\/a>, which attacks the mesothelium known as the pleura that surrounds each lung. However, mesothelioma may also occur in peritoneum (the lining of the abdominal cavity) or the pericardium (the membrane around the heart).<\/p>\n<p>Unlike some cancers, mesothelioma is difficult to detect in its infancy. <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-symptoms.html\">Mesothelioma symptoms<\/a> are typically not apparent for at least 20 years and often upward of 40 years after exposure to asbestos.<\/p>\n<p>Many initial signs of mesothelioma\u2014such as shortness of breath and chest pain\u2014are shared with numerous other medical conditions, which complicates accurate early diagnosis. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-treatment.html\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and\u2014importantly\u2014low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/asbestos-lung-cancer.html\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. There are three <a href=\"\/types-mesothelioma.html\">types of mesothelioma<\/a>, all of which target the mesothelium, a layer of tissue that covers a majority of your internal organs.<\/p>\n<p>The most common form of mesothelioma is <a href=\"\/pleural-mesothelioma.html\">pleural mesothelioma<\/a>, which attacks the mesothelium known as the pleura that surrounds each lung. However, mesothelioma may also occur in peritoneum (the lining of the abdominal cavity) or the pericardium (the membrane around the heart).<\/p>\n<p>Unlike some cancers, mesothelioma is difficult to detect in its infancy. <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-symptoms.html\">Mesothelioma symptoms<\/a> are typically not apparent for at least 20 years and often upward of 40 years after exposure to asbestos.<\/p>\n<p>Many initial signs of mesothelioma\u2014such as shortness of breath and chest pain\u2014are shared with numerous other medical conditions, which complicates accurate early diagnosis. Mesothelioma victims generally do not learn they have the condition until it is in an advanced stage.<\/p>\n<p>Although <a href=\"\/mesothelioma-treatment.html\">mesothelioma treatments<\/a> can help contain the spread of the disease and improve the comfort of victims, there is no known cure.<\/p>\n<h3>Asbestos and Mesothelioma<\/h3>\n<p>The name asbestos encompasses a group of carcinogenic, fibrous minerals that were commonplace in a variety of products and industries due to their bonding properties, insulation qualities, strength, resistance to heat and\u2014importantly\u2014low cost. Asbestos becomes dangerous when its microscopic fibers break apart, are inhaled and lodge in the lungs, which in turn can lead to mesothelioma and <a href=\"\/asbestos-lung-cancer.html\">lung cancer<\/a> among other complications.<\/p>\n<p>Occupational exposure and exposure in homes are two common sources of asbestos contamination. Because asbestos fibers are easily transferred, family members of those who worked with asbestos and brought asbestos dust home on their clothes have been known to develop mesothelioma from <a href=\"\/second-hand-asbestos.html\">second-hand asbestos exposure<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>If you or a family member was diagnosed with mesothelioma, please <a href=\"\/contact-us.html\">contact The Williams Law Firm, P.C.<\/a>\u00a0online or call 855-955-MESO (6376) for your free consultation.
